{"TopicId":159307,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Helmets","CreatedByName":"GKSP","CreatedById":160883,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-16T23:30:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GKSP","CreatedById":160883,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-16T23:30:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecently, I decided to make a jeep to use with my BDArmory save. \u00A0I ran into an issue: kerbal\u00A0helmets were just a little too big for the roof. \u00A0The heads aren\u0027t. \u00A0Instead of editing the jeep, I want to take the lazy out: remove the helmets. \u00A0I\u0027ve seen a lot of people use a mod that removes helmets from kerbals\u00A0on Kerbin, so I would like to know where to find it. \u00A0Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotaru","CreatedById":135669,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-17T00:05:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe both Texture Replacer and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E have options to remove helmets when in atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GKSP","CreatedById":160883,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-17T19:28:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223023524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159307\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492387535\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135669\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotaru\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, Hotaru said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe both Texture Replacer and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E have options to remove helmets when in atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbinchaser","CreatedById":160817,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-17T20:32:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup. I use Texture replacer. By default, it will automatically remove the helmet in a breathable atmosphere. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-18T03:10:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160883-gksp/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022160883\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160883-gksp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@GKSP\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- if you use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E you will be able to remove and even add custom helmets like in the video below ... there are also item packs with sunglasses, medieval weapons and I believe I saw something that adds beards and mustaches\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/laft3SSNyQ8?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GKSP","CreatedById":160883,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T23:38:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E, but its not working right. \u00A0Ill give texture replacer a go because its automatic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}